[For another report on this meeting in Washington, see the Des Moines
Register:
<http://www.desmoinesregister.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20080226/BUSINESS/80226038/-1/NEWS04>.

Experience shows that criticism of the messenger is usually in direct
proportion to the validity of the message and frequently reflects a
desire to deflect attention away from the topic. However,
Representative Burgess is a physician, primarily in obstetrics and
gynecology, so one can understand his proper concern about the
apparent delay. The newspaper article is significantly longer than
usual, and interested readers are advised to check the full article
on the NYT weblink. - Mod.MHJ]

